    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed at MRL 5. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels across all factors: software QA, code verification, discretization error, test conditions, output comparison, QoI relevance, validation relevance, solver error, use error, model form, model inputs, test samples, and input equivalency. Monte Carlo UQ (n=2000) confirms 95th-percentile NIH prediction remains 18% below clinical threshold. GCI-based discretization uncertainty < 4% for primary QoI. Independent peer review of model setup completed with no discrepancies. Validation performed on the identical geometry and operating conditions as the COU, providing high relevance. The structured evidence chain from foundational PIV and bench hemolysis data through uncertainty quantification to the regulatory decision is complete and traceable. Decision: Accepted.",
